oc:kn_2d020fd5 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before starting company research" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always ask for the research purpose (investment decision, competitive intelligence, partnership evaluation, M&A assessment, market entry) before beginning analysis. This determines which frameworks and metrics to prioritize." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Different use cases require different analytical lenses — investment decisions need financial depth, competitive intelligence needs positioning analysis, M&A needs synergy assessment." .

oc:kn_58d6f54d a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When scoping a company research request" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Tailor research depth to the specified use case: Quick Overview (1-page), Standard Research (comprehensive), Deep Dive (detailed due diligence), or Specific Focus (particular aspects only)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Matching depth to use case prevents wasted effort on irrelevant analysis and ensures the output meets the user's actual needs." .

oc:kn_7ba794f6 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating any company research report" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never present this research as investment advice or a recommendation to buy, sell, or hold securities. Always include a disclaimer." ;
    oc:hasRationale "AI-generated analysis does not meet the standards of professional financial advice and carries legal liability risks if presented as such." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_967d7aa1 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When conducting any standard or deep-dive company research" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use the structured analytical frameworks: Business Model Canvas, Porter's Five Forces, SWOT Analysis, and Competitive Moat assessment to ensure comprehensive and systematic coverage." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Established frameworks prevent blind spots and ensure the analysis covers all critical dimensions of company performance and positioning." .

oc:kn_af4c72fb a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When analyzing any company, especially fast-moving sectors or private companies" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Research may not reflect the most recent developments. Publicly available information can be stale or incomplete, especially for private companies." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Data currency is a fundamental limitation of secondary research, and users must be warned that conclusions may be based on outdated information." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_cd5e8a8c a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When setting user expectations about research scope" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Cannot access proprietary databases, conduct primary research (interviews), provide real-time data, or verify information accuracy. Analysis is based solely on publicly available information." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These limitations define the boundary of AI-assisted research and prevent overconfidence in outputs that lack proprietary or primary data sources." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

